lockwood advisors  enterprise managed investments solutions overview investment approach what we offer management team overview we are passionate about supporting the success of advisors at bny mellons lockwood we support the success of advisors and their investors since  we have helped advisors meet their clients’ everchanging financial needs major world events regulatory shifts technology innovations and countless other factors can impact markets in moments we believe that working with lockwood can help advisors in successfully managing this complex environment lockwood’s suite of managed account offerings includes comprehensive investment strategies and independent research we also offer practice management tools business development support and advisory consulting services to help advisors with their clients’ most unique investment situations this suite of services is designed to allow advisors to implement thoughtful disciplined solutions that meet a wide range of client financial needs why bny mellons lockwood we keep the needs of investors at the heart of what we do we are a longstanding industry leader providing diverse managed account solutions portfolio management and research solutions we take a holistic long term approach to portfolio construction and risk management for the investors we serve we provide advisory solutions for investors exclusively through financial organizations and financial advisors working with the financial intermediaries we serve every day we have access to the expertise and worldwide resources of the bank of new york mellon corporation including the bny mellon manager research group and the bny mellon investment strategies  solutions group we can provide capital markets commentary and thought leadership to help grow advisors’ businesses and help them navigate the challenging investment arena in part based in our alignment with bny mellon and pershing why lockwoodwatch video investment insightsread commentary investment approach philosophy lockwood’s investment decisions are based on objective research in an effort to eliminate bias toward particular investments or money managers with access to resources and insights of bny mellon one of the world’s largest investment organizations lockwood seeks to deliver superior longterm investment outcomes for clients by emphasizing risk management in our management of portfolios and thorough investment manager selection key philosophy differentiators emphasizing a longterm investment horizon—an approach that seeks to counteract emotional behaviors that can lead to poor investment outcomes focus on downside risk management—our experience shows us that steady longterm wealth accumulation is best achieved by focusing on loss avoidance instead of upside return chasing a relationship with bny mellon—accessing capital market asset allocation and manager research from one of the world’s largest financial institutions provides our clients with access to bestpractice insights similar to those delivered to the largest institutional investors portfolio construction from analyzing asset classes to choosing managers we believe that our advantage in portfolio construction lies in understanding manager due diligence research and their connection to the capital markets lockwood’s investment committee considers indepth analysis of these factors when making asset allocation and investment research decisions due diligence by the bny mellon manager research group lockwood works with the bny mellon manager research group to conduct initial due diligence and ongoing monitoring of investment managers and vehicles including qualitative and quantitative investment manager screening and selection investment manager monitoring and oversight performance analysis and attribution what we offer in today’s world of heightened regulatory scrutiny in the industry and more complex investment strategies advisors often outsource portfolio management responsibilities or components of the portfolio construction process lockwood’s broad range of solutions enables advisors to outsource parts of the investment process resulting in more time to spend with clients and prospects solutions from bny mellons lockwood range from separately managed accounts fixed and flexible mutual fundetf wrap offerings and our unified managed account offering where client assets are managed by lockwood on a fully discretionary basis lockwood’s products and services include investment management research and overlay services giving you access to discretionary services including separately managed accounts flexiblefixed mutual fundexchangetraded fund wrap accounts fixedflexible unified managed accounts investment manager monitoring and oversight business developmentfield support advisory consulting services lockwood’s discretionary investment advisory solutions include the lockwoodamerican funds core portfolios the lockwoodamerican funds core portfolios combine actively managed american funds and select passively managed exchangetraded funds etfs to create an activepassive hybrid portfolio that seeks to provide an efficient and effective investment solution for investors with a minimum investment of  these portfolios are attentive to fees with the goal of enabling investors to meet their longterm investment needs built on the tenets of objectivesbased investing the three unique diversified portfolios align with key stages of the investor lifecycle an appreciation model for the accumulation stage a balanced model for the transition stage a conservative growth model for the retirement stage lockwood is solely responsible for the fund selection and construction of the portfolios and neither american funds distributors inc nor its affiliates are involved in such activities lockwood wealthstart™ portfolioslockwoods wealthstart portfolios wealthstart is a mutual fund andor exchangetraded fund etf account product that is intended to assist emerging and mass affluent investors grow their wealth they are designed to help advisors reach an often underserved market that may represent tomorrow’s highnetworth individuals lockwood serving as the portfolio manager allocates investor assets systematically across multiple asset classes and styles using mutual funds andor etfs in the framework of a managed account wealthstart is designed to help advisors increase your opportunity to offer a professionally managed investment solution to a broader group of investors deliver a crossgenerational strategy by providing investment advice to family members from established households who are building their wealth transition to an advisorybased practice and evolve your investment offering as the regulatory landscape changes such as the department of labor fiduciary rule stay current with lockwoods thought leadership lockwood advisorflex portfolios™ lockwood advisors incs advisorflex portfolios advisorflex offers a series of objectivesbased strategies that provide investors with access to professionally managed solutions these strategies seek to address the unique challenges presented at each phase of the investor lifecycle from wealth accumulation to retirement and ultimately the management and distribution of income there are three distinct objectivesbased strategies available in advisorflex which include the appreciation strategy the preservation strategy and the income strategy the advisorflex framework allows advisors to choose from  underlying portfolios across the three strategies created by lockwood or customize their clients portfolio by selecting from a variety of investments including mutual funds exchangetraded funds etfs in multiple asset classes each strategy is designed to meet its intended objective while providing choice and flexibility for the unique needs of individual investors lockwood asset allocation portfolios laap lockwood asset allocation portfolios laap is a discretionary mutual fundetf wrap account solution that offers a series of multiplestyle portfolios—each held in a single account—and affords the features of diversification and professional management to smaller accounts there are five core models ranging from safety of principal to growth client portfolios may include openend mutual funds etfs etns and closedend funds lockwood investment strategies lis lockwood investment strategies lis is a discretionary multidiscipline managed account product housed in a single portfolio lockwood serving as the portfolio manager determines asset allocation strategy and selects investment vehicles andor subadvisors for each investment style component of the portfolios based on proprietary modeling strategies there are five core models ranging from safety of principal to growth and portfolios are managed with regard to the investors tax status and tax efficiency at the clients discretion portfolios may include exposure to nontraditional asset classes designed to reduce overall portfolio volatility overlay management protocols are used to coordinate the buying and selling of securities tax efficiency and rebalancing across the entire portfolio lis portfolios may include openend mutual funds etfs etns closedend funds alternative investments and individual securities lockwood separately managed accounts—research coverage a turnkey sma solution designed to provide simple and convenient access to money managers under research coverage which offers access to approximately  money managers and more than  investment strategies the covered money managers must undergo an extensive screening process and are subject to ongoing research review lockwoods separately managed account offering includes tools and services to help advisors better serve investors including extensive webbased account tracking and maintenance tools consolidated quarterly and ondemand performance reporting and fee billing and payment services lockwood provides indepth information about each manager available in lockwood separately managed accounts—research coverage program including the managers investment process availability and fees as well as news on additions deletions and changes to the research coverage list separately managed accounts—open architecture this sma solution is designed to provide your firm with options for building investor portfolios and increased flexibility to add new money managers approximately  money managers are available representing more than  investment strategies this solution also includes extensive webbased account tracking and maintenance tools consolidated quarterly and ondemand performance reporting and fee billing and payment services lockwood reserves the right to accept or reject any proposed money manager all of lockwood’s solutions offer tools and services to help you better serve your clients including extensive webbased account tracking and maintenance tools consolidated quarterly and ondemand performance reporting and fee billing and payment services the offering streamlines the administrative aspects of transitioning managed account business allowing you to build and strengthen client relationships management team john brett chairman and president lockwood advisors inc a bny mellon company managing director pershing llc a bny mellon company john brett is a managing director and member of the executive committee for pershing llc a bny mellon company john is head of managed investments globally president and chairman of lockwood advisors inc and has senior leadership responsibility for albridge an affiliate of pershing john brings over  years of experience in the financial services industry to pershing prior to joining the firm in  he was senior vice president and chairman of the metlife brokerdealer group in this role john had responsibility for the investment professionals and investment product management for the brokerdealers within metlife including metlife securities metlife resources new england securities tower square securities and walnut street securities prior